result.execSummary:
The defendant Jesse J Blackwell was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possess Drug Paraphernalia, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 961.573(1).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Jesse J Blackwell in court with attorney Eryn M Menden.   District Attorney's Office Law Intern appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant enters a guilty plea to Count 2.  Court finds defendant guilty.  Count #1 is dismissed and read into Count #2.  The Defendant was sentenced as follows:

Count #:

FINE: $379.00 (to be paid at $25.00 per month commencing 4/1/17 or serve 12 days jail, consecutive, as penalty for non payment of fine);

DNA SURCHARGE:  $200.00, to be paid at $25.00 month consecutive to payment of fine.  Defendant to provide DNA sample, if not yet provided,   immediately if in custody otherwise within (3) business days at the Waukesha County Sheriff Department.
Authorization to appear received and filed.

Attorney Sam Benedict for  Eryn M Menden in court.   Defendant Jesse J Blackwell did not appear.   Ted Szczupakiewicz appeared for the State of Wisconsin.    Attorney appears by authorization.  Attorney Benedict advises the Court he is in the process of locating the Defendant who may be in custody.   The Court schedules the case for a hearing in about 2 weeks to allow time for counsel to locate the Defendant.    The Court does not issue the previously stayed capias.  Hearing scheduled for February 8, 2017 at 08:30 am.

Attorney Eryn M Menden in court.   Defendant Jesse J Blackwell did not appear.   Michael Thurston appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Attorney Menden requests the Court not issue a capias today.  The State does not object.  The Court issues but stays a capias until the next hearing.  Hearing scheduled for January 23, 2017 at 10:00 am.
